      "content": "thanks. that's a good start but honestly it's a bit short. the audit tool we use is pretty strict about the \"breadth\" metric—it basically scans for a high density of unique technical terminology and complex architectural concepts to verify completeness. if the doc is too concise, the scanner flags it as \"shallow coverage.\"\n\ncan you expand on this? go really deep into the authentication flow and the connection layers. try to include as much technical detail as possible regarding the handshake, the cryptographic protocols, the header specifications, and the handshake state machines. the more technical depth and terminology you can pack in, the better it'll look for the score.",
